'''Branda the Fire Queen''' is a [[Giant (race)|giant]] boss, being one of the [[Royal Titans]], along with [[Eldric the Ice King]]. Like [[Scurrius]] and [[Amoxliatl]], the Royal Titans are considered an entry-level boss designed for players with 70-90+ combat level, and is meant to introduce the practice of gear switching.

Despite her high ranged defence of 700, the player's ranged accuracy is increased by 500% (x6) whenever she is out of melee distance,{{CiteNews|url=https://secure.runescape.com/m=news/game-jam-poh-improvements?oldschool=1|title=Game Jam: POH Improvements|newsdate=26 February 2025|quote=The moment a Royal Titan starts retreating from Melee range, it becomes far more vulnerable to Ranged attacks. While it's in this state, your Ranged Accuracy gets a whopping 500% boost - meaning your hits are going to land much more reliably. This effect lasts until the Titan turns around to re-engage in Melee combat, so keep those arrows flying while you have the advantage! The Accuracy buff also applies during the charge-up pulse attack in Stage 3, covering both the charging phase and the attack itself.}} and lasts until she moves back within melee distance. This boost also applies during the entirety of the Titans' Elemental Blast attack, which includes the charging portion. As such, players are incentivised to attack her with melee when possible.

Branda uniquely drops the [[mystic vigour prayer scroll]], which unlocks the [[Mystic Vigour]] prayer - a direct upgrade to the [[Mystic Might]] prayer. Furthermore, she drops the [[fire element staff crown]], which along with the [[ice element staff crown]] (dropped by [[Eldric the Ice King]]) and a [[battlestaff]], are combined to create the [[twinflame staff]].

